---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About — Bear Roll">
    <div class="px-4 py-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-xl font-bold text-heading mb-4">
            ʕ●ᴥ●ʔ About Bear Roll
        </h1>

        <p class="mb-4 text-sm">
            I'm a fan of Bear Blog's <a
                href="https://bearblog.dev/discover"
                class="text-link underline">discover page</a
            >, but I had two challenges with it. If I missed a day, good posts
            would disappear off the front pages before I ever saw them. And if I
            checked too often, I couldn't tell what was new. Basically the same
            problems that <a
                href="https://hckrnews.com"
                class="text-link underline">hckrnews.com</a
            > solves for Hacker News.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4 text-sm">
            So I built Bear Roll. Every day at midnight UTC a script grabs the
            first 5 pages of discover (100 posts) and stores them in dated
            JSON files. The result is a chronological archive of what the Bear
            Blog community has been reading and toasting.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4 text-sm">
            It's a static <a
                href="https://astro.build"
                class="text-link underline">Astro</a
            > site hosted on GitHub Pages. The source code is on <a
                href="https://github.com/joshuarichards001/bearroll"
                class="text-link underline">GitHub</a
            > if you're curious.
        </p>

        <a href="/" class="text-xs text-muted underline"
            >&larr; back to the roll</a
        >
    </div>
</Layout>
